<section id="1_section">
    <h2 class="cp-subtitle">Overview and key figures</h2>

    <p>According to OECD DAC figures, in 2014, the Netherlands provided USD 5.6 billion in net ODA, which
        represented
        0.64% of gross national income (GNI) and an increase of 1.8% in real terms from 2013. This represents a
        slight
        reversal of the downward trend in ODA volume started in 2011. ODA dropped below the 0.7% ODA/GNI target in
        2013
        for the first time since 1975 due to budgetary cutbacks in order to improve public finances. However, the
        Netherlands remains committed to the 0.7% target. The Netherlands is the sixth largest Development
        Assistance
        Committee (DAC) donor in terms of ODA as a percentage of GNI, and the seventh largest donor by volume.</p>

