    <h2 class="cp-subtitle">Priority geographical areas</h2>

    <p>The following fifteen countries will continue to be partner countries: Afghanistan - Bangladesh - Benin -
        Burundi - Ethiopia - Ghana - Indonesia - Kenya - Mali - Mozambique - the Palestinian Territories - Rwanda –
        South Sudan - Uganda and Yemen.
    </p>


    <p>Temporary assistance for the transition from development cooperation to economic cooperation will go to three
        countries: Colombia - Vietnam - and South Africa</p>


    <p>According to OECD figures, top 10 recipients of Dutch bilateral ODA in 2013-2014 were: Afghanistan, South
        Sudan, Mali, Bangladesh, Rwanda, Ghana, Syrian Arab Republic, Burundi, West Bank and Gaza Strip.</p>

